# Environment Configuration Template for Mask Generation Tools
#
# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Replace the placeholder paths below with your actual local paths
# 3. The .env file will be automatically gitignored to protect your paths

# Base directory for binary masks processing
# This should point to the BinaryMasks directory
# Example (Windows): C:\Users\YourName\project\BinaryMasks
# Example (Linux): /home/yourname/project/BinaryMasks
BINARY_MASKS_BASE=/path/to/your/BinaryMasks

# Base directory for IR measurement data
# This should point to your IR data experiment folder
# Example (Windows): D:\Data\IR_Measurements\Experiment_1
# Example (Linux): /mnt/data/IR_Measurements/Experiment_1
IR_DATA_BASE=/path/to/your/IR/data/Experiment_1

# Optional: Parent project directory
# Only needed if you're using Execution_order.md references
# Example: /path/to/project/root
# PROJECT_BASE=/path/to/your/project

# Optional: Set to 1 to suppress configuration loading messages
# QUIET=1
